Vice President Biden released a statement expressing his condolences on the passing of Senator Daniel Inouye. He described Inouye as a person who embodied courage, from his service in World War II to his time in the Senate. Biden considered Inouye to be one of the most honorable men he had ever met, and someone he trusted completely. He noted that Inouye always did what he believed was right, regardless of the consequences. Inouye also spoke about the struggles of his family and his commitment to equality throughout his life. Biden ended the statement by saying that Inouye was his friend, and he and his wife are praying for his family.